            <h2>FAQs</h2>
            <h3>What are the baggage restrictions for Spirit Airlines? </h3>
            <p>Spirit Airlines allows one personal item (small bag) for free and charges for checked and carry-on bags. Checked-bag fees vary depending on the size and weight of the bag, and carry-on fees are based on the type of ticket purchased. </p>

            <h3>What is the Spirit Airlines luggage policy? </h3>
            <p>Spirit allows one personal item (purse, laptop bag, briefcase, etc.) for free and charges for checked and carry-on bags. The size and weight of checked bags must not exceed 62 linear inches (total length + width + height) and 40 lbs, and the size of carry-on bags must not exceed 45 linear inches and 40 lbs. </p>

            <h3>Does Spirit Airlines have Wi-Fi? </h3>
            <p>Yes, Spirit offers Wi-Fi on select flights. Wi-Fi access is free and can be purchased through the Spirit app or on the aircraft. The fee is charged since they have a bare fare policy that only charges for what the customers want. </p>

            <h3>Are meals provided on Spirit Airlines flights? </h3>

            <p>No, Spirit Airlines does not provide meals on flights. Passengers may bring their food and drinks on board or purchase them from the Spirit Café onboard. The meal charges are not included, and the passengers must buy their own. </p>

            <h3>Does Spirit Airlines offer a rewards program? </h3>

